# 🧠 Concept 1: Service-Level Objectives (SLOs)

## First Understand the Problem

Imagine you built a Women Safety App.

Question:

👉 How do you know if your system is performing well?

Just saying:

```text
"App is working fine"
```

is not enough.

---

## Solution: SLO

A Service-Level Objective (SLO) is a measurable target.

Example:

```text
99.9% requests should complete
within 200 ms
```

---

## Real-World Analogy

College attendance rule:

```text
Minimum 75% attendance
```

That's an objective.

---

## Related Terms

### SLA (Service Level Agreement)

Promise to customers.

---

### SLI (Service Level Indicator)

Actual measured value.

---

### SLO (Service Level Objective)

Target value.

---

## Example

```text
SLI = 99.7% uptime

SLO = 99.9% uptime
```

---

## Why Important?

✔ Reliability

✔ User experience

✔ Performance tracking

---

## Interview Question

**Q: Difference between SLI and SLO?**

👉 SLI is the measured metric. SLO is the target value for that metric.

---

## Memory Trick

```text
Indicator = Measured

Objective = Target
```

